provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 677 (st3451): __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ dict-presence (obj[key], obj[key]=val, del obj[key])."
    - "All values False — hashlib/uuid/struct/socket types do not implement container/mapping access protocols."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __getitem__, __setitem__, or __delitem__ in its own __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not implement container/mapping protocols."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no getitem/setitem/delitem defined in its own __dict__."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

